==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Endear
<hw>En*dear"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Endeared</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Endearing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To make
dear or beloved.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧To be <xex>endeared</xex> to a
king.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To raise the price or cost of; to make costly or
expensive.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>King James I.
(1618).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Endearedly</ent>⟦br⟧
